text: What a cultural religious commentary throughout this dark comedy that plays like a Greek tragedy! The wealthy, judgmental, controlling father psychologically abuses the beautiful twins Faith and Hope, accusing them of murdering their sister Charity in the womb, and tries to force them into good behavior by keeping them away from partying with friends as teenagers, which only motivates them to think of doing him in. The exasperated mother in later years says that they were born bad and, "what haven't they done?!" Still, in contrast, Hope and Faith were the happiest in the sticks among seemingly less sophisticated people at Bible camp, where the children are happy and smiling, since they hear the contrasting original Bible message about how special, loved, wanted, good, forgiven and faultless they are in their heavenly father's eyes. Paralleling a criticism of the traditional church, Charity couldn't even survive birth into the family, Faith abandoned Hope and decided to live on her own, ragged, struggling, and detached, before threatening to bankrupt Hope and kill her child. Everyone "always knew Hope was the alpha", and Hope ultimately believes she must destroy ragged Faith in order to get out of her own debt and protect her child, the continuation of hope into the future. Hope's husband says that Hope is an enigma, since, "you can get close to her but never really feel like you can reach her".

text: Probably Paul Feig's best film. Stylish and chic - interspersed with  French sensibilities. Rides the periphery of suburban noir, dark comedy, and thriller - so it defies easy characterization; so maybe Feig created a new type of genre film with A Simple Favor. Blake Lively, channeling Marlene Dietrich (Morocco 1930), is captivating and diabolically charming. The girl oozes charisma. Speaking of her wardrobe and "turning convention" on its head; I'd love to see her cast as "The Joker" in a new Batman movie. She would kill it. This film is destined to be a cult hit that groups of girls will likely still be raving about in a decade.
